      "message": "The \"blocking calls\" from your 16966b558 was posix::stream_descriptor silently falling back to sync reads on regular file fds. The fix was moving sensor reads to random_access_file + io_uring. This patch keeps that fix. io_uring_file_service is gated on BOOST_ASIO_HAS_IO_URING alone, not on HAS_IO_URING_AS_DEFAULT.\n\n```\n // boost/asio/detail/io_uring_file_service.hpp\n #if defined(BOOST_ASIO_HAS_IO_URING)\n class io_uring_file_service : ...\n```\n\nSo PSU / Hwmon / SMBPBI / PSUEvent / Tach reads still flow through io_uring kworkers. The measurement I shared above confirms it that i2c IRQ rate is unchanged.\n\nWhat DISABLE_EPOLL additionally forces through io_uring is socket / timer / stream_descriptor traffic, all of which are epoll-able and async under epoll. The epoll itself is not \"blocking calls\". It\u0027s just a different async reactor for non-file paths.",
